MigrationHelper in org.eclipse.jface.text has this code:

public static int getBottomIndex(ITextViewer textViewer) {
	StyledText textWidget= textViewer.getTextWidget();

	if (textWidget.getClientArea().isEmpty())
		return -1;

Unfortunately, SWT/Motif does not yet special-case zero-sized widgets on Motif, so an empty client area here is {0, 0, 1, 1}.  This causes the a line index query on a negative point:

	Rectangle trim= textWidget.computeTrim(0, 0, 0, 0);
	int height= textWidget.getClientArea().height - trim.height;
	int last= getLineIndex(textWidget, height);
	int offset= textWidget.getOffsetAtLine(last);

Until bug 31563 is fixed, the text code should probably be checking for a client area of 1,1 or smaller.
